<SLUG> BC-HKN-KINGS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KINGS LOSE GOALIE CHABOT IN WAIVER DRAFT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ The Kings lost minor-league goalie Frederic Chabot
in Monday's NHL waiver draft and didn't claim any players.
</P>
<P>
   Chabot, 30, was chosen by the Montreal Canadiens. His departure
leaves Manny Legace as the third goalie in the Kings organization,
behind Stephane Fiset and Jamie Storr. Legace was assigned to the
Long Beach Ice Dogs last week.
</P>
<P>
   With the Kings losing no forwards in the waiver draft, Kings
coach Larry Robinson faces the task of deciding, perhaps as soon as
today, whether rookies Olli Jokinen and Josh Green will make the
24-man roster that will travel to Edmonton for Saturday's
regular-season opener.
</P>
<P>
   Berg update: The countdown continues for unsigned defenseman Aki
Berg, who is playing in his native Finland. If not signed by
Friday, the 21-year-old Berg will be gone for the year, because
after the season begins, he would have to clear waivers before
returning to the NHL, and it's highly unlikely that he would.
</P>
<P>
   Berg's agent, Larry Kelly of Ottawa, said he did not hear from
Kings general manager Dave Taylor on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ``At this point, the youngster fully expects to play the whole
year in Finland,'' Kelly said. ``If that happens, I think it's in
everybody's interest that he gets (traded).''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
