<P>
   POLAND-ECON (Warsaw) _ For some time now, central European
nations have been uncoupling themselves from Russia, their giant
neighbor to the east, and refocusing westward. And the breathtaking
collapse of the Russian economy, which left central Europe
standing, served to banish all doubts that this trend is for real.
By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphic clients. Photo
