<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Miss Williams, my elementary
school principal, had a framed motto hanging behind her desk.
``Don't make excuses, make good,'' it decreed. The reason I
remember it so well is because I spent a lot of time in her office
perched on the edge of the ``naughty chair'' trying to talk my way
out of my latest run-in with the rules. (Schuett, Cox News Service)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ Only a guess here, but if the current majority in
Congress had its way the Environmental Protection Agency would be
the size of an Orange Julius day crew, just without the snazzy
uniforms. (Young, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
