   GOOD _ Food shorts. (Heller, Dayton Daily News). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   GOATCHEESE _ Pure Luck, a Dripping Springs cheesemaker brought
home a handful of cheesemaking awards from the recent American
Cheese Society competition. Pure Luck, which also supplies
Jeffrey's, Si Bon , and Central market, is one of the few
cheesemakers who milks their own goats as well as makes the
cheeses. Story to follow the cheesemaking process from pasteurizing
the milk to rolling the cheeses in herbs and packaging for market.
(Crider, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   CASABLANCA _ WASHINGTON _ ``The Lisbon plane soared away from
the dense, swirling fog of Casablanca, up and into the night.'' And
so begins what author Michael Walsh jokingly calls his ``literary
suicide mission'' _ a novel that surrounds the 1942 classic film,
``Casablanca.'' The book entitled ``As Times Goes By'' is both a
sequel and a prequel to the film _ telling the story of what
happened both after and before the fateful three days when Rick and
Ilsa are so dramatically reunited and so sadly parted on the edge
of World War II. It will be published Wednesday. (Dart, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   MOVED Monday in advance in (w) Washington and (e) entertainment
categories, and will be repeated Tuesday.
</P>
