<HEADLINE>
TEXAS' RICKY WILLIAMS TO WEAR NO. 37 IN HONOR OF DOAK WALKER
</HEADLINE>
 WILLIAMS-TEX By WENDELL BARNHOUSE c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Chalk up another (unofficial) record for Ricky
Williams _ most uniform numbers in a career.
</P>
<P>
   Williams received the OK Monday to wear No. 37 to honor Doak
Walker when the Longhorns play Oklahoma Saturday in the Cotton
Bowl. Williams, who wore No. 11 his first three seasons, will
return to wearing No. 34 after the game with the Sooners.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think this will be great,'' Williams said Monday. ``I'm
wearing it because we're playing in the Cotton Bowl. I thought it
would be neat to wear 37 in the house that Doak built. I'm playing
with him in my heart. It's a special thing that I can do.''
</P>
<P>
   Texas officials had to clear the number change with the NCAA,
the Big 12 Conference and Oklahoma.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had to make sure everyone knows about it so nobody would
think we're trying to trick anyone,'' Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   Williams became friends with Walker, the former SMU star who won
the Heisman Trophy in 1948, last winter when Williams won the
running back award named for Walker. When Walker died Sept. 27,
Williams said he was dedicating the rest of his season to Walker's
memory.
</P>
<P>
   Last Saturday against Iowa State, Williams wore a No. 37 decal
on his helmet. He rushed for a Texas single-game record 350 yards.
That total, following the 318 yards Williams gained against Rice
the weekend that Walker died, made the Texas standout the first
back in NCAA history to gain 300 yards in consecutive games.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, while reading stories about Walker's career, Williams
learned that the Cotton Bowl was expanded to accommodate the crowds
that flocked to see SMU and Walker play. Even though Williams had
played Oklahoma in the Cotton Bowl three times, he was unaware the
facility was known as The House That Doak Built.
</P>
<P>
   After honoring Walker with the decal, Williams asked coach Mack
Brown if he could enhance it by wearing Walker's number. Williams
will switch numbers with Chris Robertson, who will wear 34 against
Oklahoma.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a freshman, there's not much he can really say about
it,'' Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   ``At a time where race is such an issue, here's a young black
man who is so appreciative and has a role model who was so much
older, it's just a phenomenal story,'' Texas coach Mack Brown said.
``It's just a phenomenal story. It's totally sincere and it's not a
publicity stunt.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want Ricky to do what Ricky wants to do.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-06-98 1135EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
