<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SEINFELD-CD-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOR THE `LAST TIME,' SOME OF SEINFELD'S BEST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT PHILPOT 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Print is not the best medium for Jerry Seinfeld's humor. You
lose the inflections, the way he jumps from a snap to a whine, the
way he swishes a punch line around in his mouth as if at some
comedic wine-tasting.
</P>
<P>
   It's with this disclaimer that we offer what we consider to be
some of the best lines from ``I'm Telling You for the Last Time,''
the new CD of the HBO show of Seinfeld's Broadway stand-up act. The
material isn't frighteningly original _ Shouldn't Seinfeld be above
airport jokes by now? _ but he always gives it a fresh, Seinfeldian
spin.
</P>
<P>
   ON COMMUNICATION: ``The thing that amuses me the most about
phone machines is how often we call people now, trying to get the
machine. That's what's happened now with the machine. The person
picks up and you're saying, `Uh ... oh ... I didn't think you would
be there. I just wanted to leave a message saying, `Sorry I missed
you.'''
</P>
<P>
   ON PLASTIC SURGERY: ``Friend of mine is going in for a nose job.
... Rhinoplasty, that's what they call it. ... RHINO. Is that
necessary? Person obviously is aware there's a problem. ... Do we
really need to compare them to a rhinoceros?''
</P>
<P>
   ON WOMEN: ``I know I will never understand women. I will never
understand how you can take boiling hot wax, pour it onto your
upper thigh, rip the hair out by the root _ and still be afraid of
a spider.''
</P>
<P>
   ON MEN: ``Women want to know what men are thinking. ... I will
tell you. Nothing. (Heavy applause) We're not thinking anything.
We're just walkin' around, lookin' around. This is the only natural
inclination of man.''
</P>
<P>
   ON McDONALD'S: ``Why is McDonald's still counting? How insecure
is this company? ... What is their ultimate goal _ to have cows
surrendering voluntarily? Showing up at the door, `We'd like to
turn ourselves in, we see the sign, we realize we have very little
chance out there. We'd like to be a Happy Meal, if that's at all
possible.' ''
</P>
<P>
   ON SPORTS: ``There are many things we could point to as proof
that the human being is not smart; the helmet is my personal
favorite. ... Why did we invent the helmet? Well, because we were
participating in many activities that were cracking our heads. We
looked at the situation; we chose not to avoid these activities,
but to just to make little plastic hats, so that we could continue
our head-cracking lifestyles.''
</P>
<P>
   ON CLOTHING: ``I brought this guy in a suede jacket, got spots
on it because I wore it in the rain. He says, `There's nothing we
can do. Water ruins leather.' Now _ aren't cows outdoors a lot of
the time? When it rains, do the cows go up to the farmhouse, `Hey,
hey, let us in, we're all wearing leather out here! Hey, open up,
man, I'm suede!'''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
