   TV-FALL-UPN (Undated) Reviews of new UPN drama ``Seven Days''
and new WB drama ``Charmed.''
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   LIVING-COLUMN-HAHN (Seattle) With less than three weeks to go
before our return to standard time, I'm trying desperately to save
some daylight. But most days lately seem to end with a race between
the stock market and actual daylight, trying to see which one can
close down faster.
</P>
<P>
   After carping that I'd used my hammock on only three brief
occasions this summer, I took a colleague's advice and stretched
out to enjoy one of our last sunny afternoons on the back deck.
</P>
<P>
   By Jon Hahn. (story will move in the ``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ATHLETE-TAPLIN (Seattle) Cheryl Taplin, who dominated high
school sprints in Washington while at Cleveland High School and
then won multiple All-America honors at Louisiana State, has had an
amazing summer. She's competed on three continents, earned a fair
amount of prize money and won gold medals as a member of the
winning U.S. sprint relay teams at the Goodwill Games and track's
World Cup. A career update. PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
