<P>
   COLBURN-CONSERVATORY (Los Angeles) _ Richard D. Colburn is a
demi-billionaire businessman who for the last 18 years has been the
principal patron of a respected music education program for young
people here. On Sunday, a new $28 million home of the Colburn
School of Performing Arts, which he financed, will be officially
dedicated on a site a block from the Los Angeles Music Center and
across the street from the future home of the Walt Disney Concert
Hall. The new building has already been used by nearly 1,000
after-school and summertime students from age 2{ to adults, mostly
in music but also in dance and drama. By Todd S. Purdum.
</P>
<P>
   LINCOLN-PICTURE (Undated) _ A questionable Lincoln daguerreotype
fails to sell at auction. By Judith Dobrzynski.
</P>
