<P>
   WINE-TALK (Undated) _ In the United States, ordering by the
glass did not become a widespread practice until the 1970s, when
wine first became popular among trend-setters. At first it was a
discreet way to mask one's ignorance. Murmuring ``Just a glass of
white wine please'' sounds a lot better than, ``I don't know one
wine from another.'' Now it is the way most wine is sold in
restaurants. By Frank J. Prial.
</P>
