   ANDERSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ I don't know exactly how it happened. It must have
started normally enough, probably with comfortable furnishings
purchased more for their practicality and durability than their
aesthetic value. But a couple of episodes of Martha Stewart and a
few articles in some decorating magazines changed all of that.
Before I knew it, I had started buying frames that cost more than
the pictures inside them. We had white chairs in the dining room.
... By MONICA ANDERSON. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
