<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The Capeside quartet: Who's who on `Dawson's Creek'
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   James van der Beek
</P>
<P>
   Plays: Dawson Leery, earnest, super-sensitive young filmmaker
and Steven Spielberg acolyte who's caught in a love triangle.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 21
</P>
<P>
   Hometown: Cheshire, Conn.
</P>
<P>
   On being like Dawson: ``Dawson's a lot like I was at 15. I can
do this character more justice than I could at 15 'cause I have
distance on all those terribly painful adolescent traumas that
everybody goes through.''
</P>
<P>
   Currently reading: ``Life After God'' by Douglas Copeland.
</P>
<P>
   Movie career: Stars as a high school quarterback with Jon Voight
in ``Varsity Blues,'' coming in January. ``I cut off my hair, dyed
it black, gained about 15 pounds of muscle and used a Texas accent.
I tried to get as far away from Dawson as I could.''
</P>
<P>
   Katie Holmes
</P>
<P>
   Plays: Joey Potter, Dawson's longtime platonic friend and
budding romantic interest
</P>
<P>
   Age: 19
</P>
<P>
   Hometown: Toledo, Ohio
</P>
<P>
   On being like Joey: ``I guess I'm kind of a tomboy. I wasn't
that into dating in high school.''
</P>
<P>
   Currently reading: ``Pride and Prejudice'' by Jane Austen. ``I'd
love to play Elizabeth Bennett.''
</P>
<P>
   Movie career: Starred in summer teen-horror flick ``Disturbing
Behavior.'' Will appear in ``Killing Mrs. Tingle,'' a dark teen
comedy by ``Dawson'' creator Kevin Williamson.
</P>
<P>
   Joshua Jackson
</P>
<P>
   Plays: Pacey Witter, sarcastic sidekick to Dawson.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 20
</P>
<P>
   Hometown: Vancouver, British Columbia
</P>
<P>
   On being like Pacey: Like Pacey, Jackson is an upbeat, energetic
joker with deceptive depth. ``There's not very much acting involved
for something that's this intensive. A lot of this stuff is just
what comes naturally to me.''
</P>
<P>
   Currently reading: ``Why I Am Not a Christian'' by Bertrand
Russell, which he bought at Hartsfield International Airport while
changing planes in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Movie career: Stars in teen-horror flick ``Urban Legend,'' which
finished sixth nationally and fourth in metro Atlanta in the latest
weekend box office figures. Will appear in ``Apt Pupil,'' debuting
Oct. 23.
</P>
<P>
   Michelle Williams
</P>
<P>
   Plays: Jennifer Lindley, former New York bad girl who's moved to
Capeside to remake herself, and tempt Dawson.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 18
</P>
<P>
   Hometown: Kalispell, Mont.
</P>
<P>
   On being like Jen: ``I think Jen is the most misunderstood
character ... (and) I feel sort of misunderstood. Our pasts are
similar in that I left home really early and so did she.''
</P>
<P>
   Currently reading: ``Letters From a War Zone,'' a collection of
feminist essays by Andrea Dworkin and ``Juliette'' by the Marquis
de Sade. ``The balance between the two is really interesting. I
wouldn't want to read one alone without the other.''
</P>
<P>
   Movie career: ``Starred in `Halloween H20' with Jamie Lee
Curtis. Will co-star with Kirsten Dunst in ``Dick,'' a 1999 comedy
about teenagers snooping in the Nixon White House.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
