   SF-NORTH-BEACH (San Francisco) _ San Francisco's North Beach is
back. It started slowly, with a restaurant here and a cafe there.
But in the last year the North Beach movement has picked up steam.
Restaurants are opening at a stunning rate, and once moribund shops
and bakeries are packed. And why not? The neighborhood has charm.
It has history. It is one of San Francisco's sunniest areas and it
is just a short walk from the financial district or Fisherman's
Wharf. More important, North Beach has character. By Ruth Reichl.
</P>
