<P>
   LEFT FIELD: Greg Vaughn
</P>
<P>
   Talk about your comeback of the year story. The Padres tried to
unload him on the Yankees last season, but a shoulder injury caused
him to flunk their physical. Rather than go into a funk, Vaughn
took it out on NL clubs this year by smacking a club-record 50 home
runs. He also drove in a career-best 119 RBIs.
</P>
<P>
