</P>
<P>
   He provides the Padres a Gold Glove-caliber center fielder, but
he's not in the class of Andruw Jones. His offensive numbers were
down considerably off the last two seasons, and hit a woeful .188
against left-handers. Look for ex-Yankees farmhand Ruben Rivera to
possibly draw the start against lefty Tom Glavine.
</P>
