</P>
<P>
   If the Padres need a fourth starter, Hamilton get the nod, and
he'll work out of the bullpen early in the series. The Atlanta
resident is a solid third or fourth starter _ going 13-13, 12-7 and
15-9 the past three years. What's deceiving about his wins this
season is his run-support of 3.4 a start was second fewest in the
NL. The Braves have knocked him around pretty hard.
