</P>
<P>
   The Padres have the game's best closer in Trevor Hoffman, who
converted 53 of 54 save opportunities. One of the reasons San Diego
acquired Randy Myers and his $6 million contract was a fear that
the Braves might get him. Well, the veteran lefty didn't face a
hitter in the just completed series. Instead, the main setup man
for Hoffman has been righty Dan Miceli, who pitched out of trouble
in three games against Houston.
