<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 7
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-AUTRY-NYT (moved on Friday, October 2)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Gene Autry sent by the New York Times News
Service on Friday, October 2, misstated the history of singing
cowboys in the movies. He was not the first; Ken Maynard was,
singing in the 1929 western ``The Wagon Master.'' Mr. Autry first
sang in Maynard's 1934 film ``In Old Santa Fe.''
</P>
</TEXT>
