<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-06 23:53 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3178 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-CSUN-LADN     10-06 0516
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-CSUN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURY SLOW TO SHOW
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Twenty minutes after practice began Tuesday, Cal
State Northridge defensive end Patrick Cwik pulled himself out with
a sore neck.
</P>
<P>
   Cwik is fortunate he even made it to practice at all.
</P>
<P>
   A junior starter, Cwik said he was riding his bike from the main
campus to North Campus Stadium earlier in the day when he was hit
by a car. The incident took place in front of the Asian House on
Halsted Street.
</P>
<P>
   ``I flew off the windshield and went flying,'' said Cwik,
sporting a cut beneath his nose. ``The lady was hysterical. She
never saw me coming. I got up, didn't break anything, so I told her
not to worry about it. I don't know who it was.''
</P>
<P>
   Cwik didn't tell the coaching staff about the accident until he
took himself out of practice. He spent the rest of the time with
ice on the back of his neck. Cwik said team trainers thought he may
have whiplash. Police were not called to the scene.
</P>
<P>
   ``He said, `Hey, I'm fine,''' CSUN coach Ron Ponciano said. ``He
doesn't even want to indicate that he can't play football.''
</P>
<P>
   Cwik said he will try to practice today and remains optimistic
he will be available for No.23 CSUN's showdown Saturday with No.18
Montana. However, if he can't play against the Grizzlies (3-2, 2-1
Big Sky), it will pose enormous problems for the Matadors'
defensive line.
</P>
<P>
   Not only are Sean Beard (broken leg) and Marcus Nance (knee)
out, Ponciano said it's unlikely Mike Colunga (ankle) will play.
Also, Jacob Mageo (pinched nerve) didn't practice so Quinton Reed,
a 6-foot-2, 270-pound junior, was shifted from linebacker to nose
guard.
</P>
<P>
   ``How many more guys can we lose?'' Ponciano said.
``Fortunately, we have a lot of guys that can play multiple
positions.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think (Reed) will be a great defensive lineman. You get a
guy in there that's fresh and can get off the ball quickly, that's
of the utmost importance.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Nice shirt, coach: The first national ranking since CSUN
moved to Division I-AA left many of the Matadors in jovial moods
before practice, and Ponciano sensed it. So he went on the
offensive about getting everyone's attention back on Big Sky power
Montana.
</P>
<P>
   And he did so by donning a Montana Grizzlies T-shirt.
</P>
<P>
   ``I put it on and got in a bad mood quickly,'' Ponciano said.
``The reality is we have Montana coming up, so we can't afford to
slip.''
</P>
<P>
   __ First downs: Center Beau Cherry, who injured his knee in the
season opener at Boise State, returned to practice Tuesday and will
back up Julio Alcala. Also, Mike Barnes (groin) practiced after
missing Saturday's game with Southern Utah.... Ponciano said
little-used defensive back Bryant Eubanks quit the team Tuesday for
lack of playing time.... Backup defensive back James Maldonado
(pinched nerve) and linebacker Carl Finely (shoulder) missed
practice.... Wide receiver Eric Carpenter (ankle) returned to
practice after missing two weeks but said he doesn't expect to play
against Montana.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
